chapter.para:
Angle-bracket enclosure is also used to indicate that a term stands for
some random member of a larger class (this is straight
from BNF). Examples like the following are common:

The schwa vowel is omitted in syllables containing vocalic r, l, m or n;
that is, ‘kitten’ and ‘color’ would be rendered
/kit'n/ and /kuhl'r/, not /kit'&schwa;n/ and /kuhl'&schwa;r/.

